Implicit user modeling for personalized search has been  studied in previous work, but our work differs from all previous work in several aspects: (1) We emphasize the exploitation of  immediate search context such as the related immediately preceding query and the viewed documents in the same session, while most previous work relies on long-term collection of implicit feedback  information [25].
